Key Match Events: Achraf Hakimi missed a late penalty, leading to Morocco's elimination.
South Africa scored two goals, including one by Themba Zwane and another by Teboho Mokoena.
Post-Match Reflections: Morocco's players and coach expressed disappointment over the missed penalty and the loss.
South Africa's players celebrated their victory, advancing to the quarter-finals.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Morocco's defeat means none of the top five African teams will progress to the quarter-finals.
Mali's victory over Burkina Faso sends them to the quarter-finals for the first time since 2013.
